==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: degauss
<hw>de*gauss"</hw> <pr>(d⟦esl⟧*gous")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To make a (steel) ship's hull nonmagnetic by applying an opposing
magnetic field.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To remove irregular magnetization in (the electron
gun of a cathode-ray tube); -- used to improve picture quality,
especially in computer monitors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>degaussing</ent>⟦br⟧
